  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:56:19.582Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Logit bias",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " adds a fixed offset to specific token logits before softmax, making some tokens more or less likely without changing model weights. APIs accept a map of token ID \u2192 bias value. Agents use logit bias sparingly to nudge format tokens (JSON braces, newlines) or suppress undesired patterns\u2014 not as a substitute for prompting or constrained decoding."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Logit bias diagram showing token probability adjustment before and after applying bias values"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For token id i, effective logit z'\u1d62 = z\u1d62 + bias\u1d62. Bias is typically in [-100, 100] on OpenAI-compatible APIs; extreme negative bias effectively bans a token. Requires knowing tokenizer token IDs for target strings."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When structured output modes are unavailable, small biases can increase the chance of starting JSON with \"{\" or ending tool calls with valid delimiters. Negative bias can reduce repetition tokens or block known toxic substrings at the token level. Misuse can corrupt grammar or produce invalid syntax."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tokenize the target string, look up IDs via the provider tokenizer, set bias entries, pass logit_bias in the completion request. Biases apply at every generation step\u2014 a globally banned token cannot appear anywhere in the output, which may break code or URLs containing that substring as a token fragment."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import tiktoken\nenc = tiktoken.encoding_for_model(\"gpt-4o-mini\")\n\ndef bias_for_string(s, value=-100):\n    return {enc.encode(s)[0]: value}  # first subword only\u2014check full tokenization\n\nbias = {}\nbias.update(bias_for_string(\"\\n\\nHuman:\", -100))  # suppress fake role injection\nbias.update({enc.encode(\"{\")[0]: 5})               # mild nudge toward JSON\n\n# pass logit_bias=bias to the API"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fine-grained nudge without retraining or long prompt prefixes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Can suppress specific token sequences at inference"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Works alongside temperature and top-p"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Token IDs are model- and tokenizer-specific\u2014not portable"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Subword tokenization means biasing a string requires multiple IDs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Over-strong bias breaks fluency and valid outputs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Constrained decoding and JSON mode are safer for structure when available"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prefer grammar-based or JSON-schema constrained decoding for agent tool payloads. Consider logit bias for legacy endpoints, stopping unwanted role tokens, or experiments. Avoid large negative biases on common subwords (e.g., \" the\") that appear inside many tokens."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agentic AI connection"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Some agent frameworks apply dynamic bias during tool-call phases only\u2014implemented by splitting generation calls rather than biasing an entire long completion. Safer pattern: separate system/user messages and use response_format or tool-choice API fields instead of manual logit maps."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Biasing English words without checking BPE splits across models"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Using -100 on tokens that appear inside required JSON keys"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Applying static bias across all agent steps including natural-language user replies"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Expecting logit bias to enforce multi-token constraints (unclosed brackets)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Print tokenization for target strings before setting bias"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Keep bias magnitudes small (+1 to +5) for nudges; reserve extremes for bans"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Test agent evals after any bias change\u2014regressions are subtle"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prefer first-class structured output APIs over manual bias maps"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Logit bias shifts token logits before softmax at inference"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Requires per-model token IDs; subword effects are easy to get wrong"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Useful for mild nudges and bans, not full schema enforcement"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Agents should prefer constrained decoding and tool APIs over heavy bias"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}